cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with visual recognition and 3D reconstruction, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of egomotion-aware feature warping and depth-aware unprojection operations suggests that the paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO). The proposed models are neural networks, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on learning from experience suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
